<promed@promedmail.org>

[As this article points out, the clinical signs of rabies in raccoons
vs those of distemper in raccoons are very different. Raccoons with
distemper are not aggressive, but may have trouble walking or even
staying in a tree. On the other hand, raccoons with rabies are very
aggressive.

While there are 2 types of rabies, one being aggressive (the furious
form) and one being very passive (the dumb form), the passive form is
seldom seen in raccoons.

Vaccinating your pets against rabies and distemper is very important.
Pet care and personal health care are not areas to cut back on in
times of economic down turn. - Mod.TG]

The state of Florida in the southeastern US can be seen on the
